Package: measureR
Title: Shiny Application for Educational and Psychological Measurement
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R:
    c(
      person(
        given = "Hasan",
        family = "Djidu",
        email = "hasandjidu@gmail.com",
        role = c("aut", "cre"),
        comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1110-6815")
      )
    )
Description: Provides an interactive Shiny-based toolkit for educational and psychological measurement supporting content validity, dimensionality assessment, Classical Test Theory (CTT) using the 'CTT' package (Willse, 2018) <doi:10.32614/CRAN.package.CTT>, Item Response Theory (IRT) via 'mirt' (Chalmers, 2012) <doi:10.18637/jss.v048.i06>, Exploratory Factor Analysis through 'psych' (Revelle, 2025), and Confirmatory Factor Analysis and Structural Equation Modeling based on the 'lavaan' framework (Rosseel, 2012) <doi:10.18637/jss.v048.i02>, allowing users to upload data, evaluate models, visualize results, and export outputs through an intuitive graphical interface without programming.
